Package agents

Contains the classes that define agents in the simulation, including the two types of peer and other agents like the Runner and the Host Cache.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicAgent
    A common set of behaviours for all agents in the system.
    HostCache
    The Host Cache is responsible for adding new peers to a list of connected peers and supplying peers with a list of Super Peers in the network.
    OrdinaryPeer
    Ordinary Peers have a limited set of functionality compared with Super Peers, but are more common in the network.
    Peer
    Behaviour of all peers, both Ordinary and Super
    Runner
    Runs the simulation, and keeps track of information about the network.
    SuperPeer
    A Super Peer has more bandwidth, and thus more responsibilities in the network.
